# Contribution Workflow

> This rule describes the complete contribution process for the project, from getting started to release. It provides a step-by-step guide for new contributors, explains the development workflow, code review expectations, and release procedures to ensure smooth collaboration.

This rule outlines the workflow for contributing to the rudder-cli project.

## Getting Started

1. Read the [CONTRIBUTING.md](mdc:CONTRIBUTING.md) file for guidelines
2. Check the [CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md](mdc:CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md) for community standards

## Development Workflow

1. Fork the repository and create a feature branch
2. Make your changes following the project's coding standards
3. Write tests for your changes
4. Run tests with `make test`
5. Build the CLI with `make build`
6. Submit a pull request

## Code Review Process

- All pull requests must pass CI checks
- Code owners will review your PR as specified in [CODEOWNERS](mdc:CODEOWNERS)
- Address review comments and update your PR as needed

## Release Process

- Releases are managed using the [.goreleaser.yaml](mdc:cli/.goreleaser.yaml) configuration
- Releases are automatically built and published for multiple platforms
